BANKNOTES PROBLEM SET

The bank note data contains several measures from both authentic and counterfeit bank notes. Use the tools and concepts introduced to study the dataset and see to what extent: + counterfeit bills can be identified by the measures given in the data + counterfeit bills tend to be unusual?

library(GGally)
library(ggplot2)

banknote <- read.csv("~/GitHub/explore/data/banknote.csv")

ggplot(aes(x = Top, y = Diagonal), data = banknote) + geom_point()

#After plotting the original ggpairs, I divided them into two groups. 
banknote$group <- ifelse(banknote$Diagonal >= 140.5, "X", "Y")

ggpairs(banknote, 1:7, colour = "group")
